First, install the `dox` library using `vcpkg` or `conan` package manager. Then, include the necessary headers and link against the library.

```cpp
#include <string>
#include <markdown/markdown.h>

std::string markdownToHtml(const std::string& markdown) {
    Markdown md;
    std::string html = md.markdownToHtml(markdown);
    return html;
}
```

In this function, we create an instance of `Markdown` class, pass the markdown text to `markdownToHtml` method, and return the resulting HTML string.

**Note:** This implementation assumes that you have installed the `dox` library correctly and linked against it. If you're using an IDE, make sure to add the necessary library paths and include directories to your project settings.

**Alternative Implementation using Regular Expressions:**
If you don't want to use an external library, you can implement a simple Markdown parser using regular expressions. This implementation will be limited to basic Markdown syntax conversion (e.g., headers, bold text, links, lists).

```cpp
#include <string>
#include <regex>
#include <sstream>

std::string markdownToHtml(const std::string& markdown) {
    std::string html;
    std::stringstream ss(markdown);

    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(ss, line)) {
        // Headers
        std::regex headerRegex("^#+(.*)$");
        std::smatch match;
        if (std::regex_match(line, match, headerRegex)) {
            html += "<h" + std::to_string(match.size() - 1) + ">" + match[1] + "</h" + std::to_string(match.size() - 1) + ">\n";
            continue;
        }

        // Bold text
        std::regex boldRegex("^\\*([^\\*]+)\\*$");
        if (std::regex_match(line, match, boldRegex)) {
            html += "<b>" + match[1] + "</b>\n";
            continue;
        }

        // Links
        std::regex linkRegex("^\\[(.+?)\\]\\((.+?)\\)$");
        if (std::regex_match(line, match, linkRegex)) {
            html += "<a href=\"" + match[2] + "\">" + match[1] + "</a>\n";
            continue;
        }

        // Lists
        std::regex listRegex("^\\s*\\d+\\.\\s+(.*)$");
        if (std::regex_match(line, match, listRegex)) {
            html += "<li>" + match[1] + "</li>\n";
            continue;
        }

        // Normal text
        html += line + "\n";
    }

    return html;
}
```

**Note:** This implementation is limited to basic Markdown syntax conversion and may not cover all edge cases. For a more comprehensive Markdown parser, consider using an external library like `dox`.

